            {
              "lessonId": "recPeN4ndxTC8lWmI",
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 1,
              "weekLabel": "Week 1",
              "sequence": 1,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 1",
              "title": "10m Written Narration: Grade 3 - Lesson 1",
              "body": "➜ WRITTEN NARRATION \nComplete one written narration this week (or start every other week). Make sure to write from a variety of different subjects, either over the course of the term or at least the year.\n\nIt is common for students to fatigue quickly when first beginning written narration. Allow them to initially write a bit and tell the rest. Some may do better by first orally narrating and discussing as usual, then writing a sentence or so of that narration. Others may do better by beginning their narration in writing, then completing orally.",
              "teacherNotes": "★ TEACHER NOTE\nWritten narrations can happen at the end of any lesson if time allows and do not need to take up an extra 10 minutes in your schedule. This tracker just serves to remind you to start the habit.",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=reckE0OR0ILeJX6TV&6J82c=recPeN4ndxTC8lWmI",
